Parliament, Monday, 1 February 2021 – The Select Committee on Finance will tomorrow morning hold a two-hour virtual meeting, from 09:30 to 12:00, to be briefed by the National Treasury on the Audit Profession Amendment Bill [B2-2020].
	
	The Bill was first processed by the Standing Committee on Finance, which adopted a committee report on 17 November 2020. It was later debated and adopted by the National Assembly on 2 December 2020.
	
	The Bill is to amend the Auditing Profession Act of 2005, so as to insert a definition and, amongst other things, to strengthen the governance of the regulatory board, and to strengthen investigating and disciplinary processes.
	
	Members of the public may get involved and follow committee sittings live on Parliament TV (DStv Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
